<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0548 </DOCNO><TEXT>The structure of the oil market is changing and changing fast. The priceof crude may be highly volatile on the basis of figures supplied by thespot market. The Nymex in particular may be booming. Yet a rapid processof reintegration is going on. Term contracts are once again becomingpopular. Downstream is beginning once again to match upstream. For allits seasonal, monthly and daily swings, the price of a wet barrel ofoil does not look like plunging. And above all, it is profoundly mistakento take the well-worn popular view that Opec is in crisis.</TEXT></DOC>